<P>
FEDERAL EXPRESS JET LANDS SAFELY AFTER WORKER ATTACKS CREW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Federal Express employee armed with a hammer and a spear gun attacked the 
flight crew of a company cargo plane Thursday before the crew wrestled him to 
the floor and safely landed the plane. 
</P>
<P>
 Three people aboard the DC-10, including the attacker, were critically hurt, 
and a fourth suffered less serious injuries, said Rick Roberts of the Regional 
Medical Center in Memphis. 
</P>
<P>
 Airport Authority President Larry Cox said the crew members suffered head and 
body injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 "They were very bloody," Cox said. "It looked like they had been in an 
explosion or a film you would see of Vietnam. . . . It must have been 
hand-to-hand combat." 
</P>
<P>
 The attacker was a company pilot but not a member of the plane's crew, said 
officials of Federal Express, which allows its employees to ride free if room 
is available. 
</P>
<P>
 An FBI agent said the assailant would be held on federal charges of attacking 
an aircraft crew. His motive was unclear. The plane was bound for San Jose, 
Calif. 
</P>
