<HEADLINE>
<P>
ESCALON TO CLOSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am a teacher at Escalon Center in Altadena. Our campus serves a population 
of students who have been labeled severely emotionally disturbed and/or 
unmanageable by the school district.Many of our students come from abusive 
homes and impoverished communities. These children have been dismissed from 
public schools for a variety of reasons; since 1959, Escalon has been there to 
provide a place for these forgotten students.  
</P>
<P>
 In addition to academic services, Escalon provides counseling, social programs 
and community outreach programs, so that our students have the best chance 
possible for happy, successful lives. 
</P>
<P>
 In June, Escalon will be forced to close its doors forever, due to 
overwhelming financial difficulties. I believe this to be a monumental tragedy. 
In addition to a number of dedicated staff members now facing the prospect of 
unemployment, over 80 students who have worked very hard to be a part of 
something and better themselves will be forced to start over, learn to trust 
all over again, or be left with nothing and nowhere to go. 
</P>
<P>
 LeANN SLOUGH 
</P>
<P>
 Escalon Center, Altadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
