<TEXT>
<P>
 Tennis  
</P>
<P>
 The Dutch are expected to announce Monday that they will build a temporary 
12,500-capacity stadium along the waterfront in Rotterdam for a quarterfinal 
Davis Cup match against the United States July 15-17. 
</P>
<P>
 The matches will be played on a hardcourt surface. 
</P>
<P>
 Second-seeded Sergi Bruguera advanced to the quarterfinals of the Conde de 
Godo ATP tournament in Barcelona with a 6-4, 6-4 victory over Alberto 
Berasategui. Bruguera, the French Open champion, will play seventh-seeded 
Richard Krajicek, who beat Andrei Chesnokov, 7-6 (9-7), 6-3. Soccer  
</P>
<P>
 Joao Havelange, the FIFA president, is proposing to increase the number of 
teams in the World Cup to 32 from 24 for the 1998 tournament in France. 
</P>
<P>
 Havelange, trying to win the votes necessary for a sixth four-year term, 
promised to increase the numbers of teams from Asia and the North and Central 
American and Caribbean region to three each, from two, without taking spots 
away from Europe, which has 13 berths. 
