<P>
COLLEGE VOLLEYBALL; TOP TEAMS IN UCLA TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UCLA men's volleyball tournament, which begins tonight at Pauley Pavilion, 
will feature four teams ranked among the top 14 in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
 Fourth-ranked USC will play No. 14 Loyola Marymount at 5, and top-ranked UCLA 
will face sixth-ranked Cal State Northridge at 7. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA's semifinal against Northridge (14-8) is the only match in the tournament 
that will count as a Mountain Pacific Sports Federation match. The Bruins 
(20-1) are led by Jeff Nygaard, whose averages of 1.94 blocks and 7.11 kills a 
game rank him second and third, respectively, in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
 The third-place match will be held at 5 Saturday, followed by the championship 
match at 7:30. WENDY WITHERSPOON 
