<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; CONRAD SETS SCHOOL SHOTPUT RECORD IN BREA-OLINDA GIRLS' TRACK VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marsha Conrad broke a 9-year-old school shotput record and helped Brea-Olinda 
to a 93-34 victory over Magnolia in an Orange League track and field meet 
Thursday at Brea-Olinda. 
</P>
<P>
 Conrad's mark of 35 feet 6 inches breaks Kim Dearman's 1985 record of 34-2 
1/2. It also comes on the heels of the junior's record-breaking discus mark 
last week in the Brea Unocal relays. Conrad's mark of 113-5 broke her school 
record from last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda improved to 5-3, 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Orange League meet: 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 73, Western 25 -- Jenny Gonzales won the 800 (2:48) and 1,600 
(6:29.5) for Valencia (2-1, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 97, Orange 25 -- Dawn Brown took first in the 200 (27.7) and 400 
(1:00.6) for Canyon (2-0, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 70, Loara 57 -- For Loara (2-2, 0-2), Pearl Mercer won the 100 
(12.8) and 200 (27.4), and Ellen Hsu won the long jump (13-9 3/4) and triple 
jump (31-4). 
</P>
<P>
