<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES; BOYS' SOCCER COACH AT CANYON RESIGNS AFTER STRONG SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canyon boys' soccer Coach Ali Khosroshahin, who led the Comanches to one of 
their best seasons, has resigned, the school announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Khosroshahin coached the Comanches for two seasons. He was named the Century 
League coach of the year after leading Canyon to the league championship this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Comanches finished 16-6-3 and advanced to the second round of the Southern 
Section Division II playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 University High's James Stephenson, a two-time Sea View League champion in 
wrestling and a Southern Section runner-up this year with a record of 49-6 at 
145 pounds, will attend Columbia University with the intention of wrestling at 
the school. 
</P>
