WEST VENTURA COUNTY EDITION: VENTURA; MAN HURT IN FALL OFF ROOF OF COUNTY 
OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 30-year-old man was injured early Thursday when he fell from the roof of 
county offices behind Ventura City Hall, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A Ventura police officer found fall victim Brian Mahoney and Paul Belman, 30, 
outside the county offices about 2 a.m., according to Ventura Police Lt. David 
Ingles. 
</P>
<P>
 After talking to the men and noticing a broken window next to the roof from 
which Mahoney fell, police arrested Belman on suspicion of attempted burglary. 
Because of his injuries, Mahoney was not arrested, Ingles said, adding that he 
believes the men were from outside the area. 
</P>
<P>
 Mahoney was listed in stable condition at Ojai Valley Hospital late Thursday. 
He sustained hip and shoulder injuries, according to fire officials. 
</P>
<P>
 Employees at the Ventura County Public Social Services Agency said they were 
baffled by the incident and could find nothing missing from their offices. 
</P>
<P>
 "We got a call around 2:30 this morning that someone had fallen trying to 
break in here," said Jim Isom, director of public social services. "We think 
they may have been trying to get into City Hall." 
</P>
<P>
 Isom said the only evidence that something was amiss was the broken window 
along the corridor that connects the county office to City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't know what they were doing on the roof," Isom said. "But I'm sure at 2 
a.m., their goals were not honorable." MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
