<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: ARUM BUYS OUT GOOSSEN OPERATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SEAN WATERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top Rank Boxing has purchased the Ten Goose operation in Van Nuys, including 
the contracts of Rafael Ruelas, the International Boxing Federation lightweight 
champion, and his brother Gabriel, promoter Bob Arum said Thursday in Beverly 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Goossen, former head of Ten Goose, was named executive vice president of 
Top Rank Boxing and will manage the Olympic Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
 "This move is something I could only have done with Arum," Goossen said. 
"We've been on opposite sides of the fence when it comes to negotiating, but 
we've always been friends." 
</P>
<P>
 For 13 years, Goossen was president and promoter of Ten Goose, putting on 
shows with his family at the Country Club in Reseda. Those shows will no longer 
be held. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm bringing Danny aboard because he is an experienced boxing man who knows 
this area well," Arum said. SEAN WATERS 
</P>
