<TEXT>
<P>
 President Clinton slipped and fell in mud during his regular morning jog 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The President, who was almost two miles into a three-mile run, slipped and 
fell on a muddy incline near the Tidal Basin in northwest Washington and soiled 
his long-sleeved white T-shirt, turquoise shorts and left leg. 
</P>
<P>
 "He slipped and fell and got right back up," said a woman who ran with 
