</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Money Supply Mixed: The Federal Reserve Board reported that the measure of the 
nation's money supply know as M2 rose in the week ended March 28 to a 
seasonally adjusted $3,586.2 billion, up $100 million from a revised $3,586.1 
billion the week before.A broader measure, M3, fell $4.3 billion to $4,212.0 
billion from $4,216.3 billion. The narrowest measure, M1, rose $3.2 billion to 
$1,146.4 billion from $1,143.2 billion. M1 includes cash in circulation, 
deposits in checking accounts and non-bank traveler's checks. M2 is M1 plus 
accounts like savings deposits and money-market mutual funds. M3 is M2 plus 
less-liquid accounts, such as certificates of deposit in minimum denominations 
of $100,000. 
</P>
