Prenovost Jr. of Santa Ana. "We believe he moved out of state two or three 
months ago. We think he might be in Florida." 
</P>
<P>
 Bank of Newport had no idea Rodgers was gone. The bank had sued Rodgers in 
January, alleging that he and his secretary lived the high life on bank expense 
accounts. Rodgers later married his secretary, Verna Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
 Stephen M. Magro of Orange, who represents Rodgers in the Bank of Newport suit 
only, said he is in touch with Rodgers, but he refused to say where his client 
might be. Rodgers has denied all the allegations in the Bank of Newport 
lawsuit. 
