<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: ROSEMEAD; BODIES OF 3 
DISCOVERED IN APPARENT MURDER-SUICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The bodies of an El Monte shoe repair shop owner, his wife and their 
16-month-old son were found in a Rosemead apartment Wednesday night, 
authorities said. It is believed that the man killed his wife and son with a 
handgun before turning the weapon on himself. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives suspect that the man, identified by the county coroner's office as 
Parviz Parvand, 39, fired the shots after a domestic dispute, said Los Angeles 
County Sheriff's Deputy Angie McLaughlin. Bruises and cuts were found on the 
bodies of Rocio Carmen Parvand, 33, and the boy, Alex Parvand, sheriff's 
detectives told neighbors. 
</P>
<P>
 A handgun was found at the scene and detectives believe it was fired by the 
husband, McLaughlin said. The bodies were discovered at about 9:30 p.m. by 
Rocio Parvand's parents, who had dropped by the apartment in the 9400 block of 
Steele Street to visit their daughter, said neighbor Leticia Nieto. 
</P>
