<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SIGNAL HILL; MINISTER 
FINDS INFANT IN BAG ON CHURCH DOORSTEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police were searching Thursday for the parents of a baby that a minister found 
in a vinyl bag at the front door of his Signal Hill church. 
</P>
<P>
 The pastor's dog sniffed out the infant about 5:25 a.m. at Signal Hill First 
Baptist Church at 1948 E. 20th St. The baby was wrapped in a towel and tucked 
in the bag, said police Detective Mary Risinger. 
</P>
<P>
 Police took the child to Long Beach Memorial Medical Center, where he was in 
good condition. 
</P>
<P>
 The child, weighing six pounds, was less than a day old and had probably been 
on the church steps no more than two hours, authorities said. The county 
Department of Children's Services will find a home for the baby, Risinger said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
