<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN JAILED IN HIJACKING OF BIG RIG TRUCK; INVESTIGATION: AUTHORITIES SAY 
SUSPECT HAD PROBLEMS DRIVING THE VEHICLE AND WAS PURSUED BY OTHER TRUCKERS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS ALGER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A San Clemente man is in jail in lieu of $100,000 bail after discovering a big 
rig is tougher to drive than it looks, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Du Bois, 25, is charged with hijacking a tractor-trailer truck 
Wednesday from the Whittaker brake-check facility on the Golden State Freeway 
north of Castaic. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect drove to the site in a car at about 2 p.m. and became angry when 
none of the truck drivers he attempted to flag down would stop to pick him up, 
said California Highway Patrol Officer Wendy Moore of the Newhall office. The 
CHP doesn't know why Du Bois abandoned the car or wanted a ride. 
</P>
<P>
 Du Bois walked in front of a big rig driven by Domingo Palomo, 32, of Delano 
and fired one shot from a .44-magnum handgun into the pavement, Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 CHP reports indicate Palomo was in the truck cab when the gun was fired, but a 
witness said Palomo was standing in front of the vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
 "The guy fired a round at the driver between his legs and the driver jumped 
back and let him have it (the truck)," said Richard Hyer, a driver from Akron, 
Ohio. "And I don't blame him." 
</P>
<P>
 Du Bois allegedly climbed into the big rig and drove it south on the Golden 
State Freeway, with Hyer and other truckers in pursuit. 
</P>
<P>
 But apparently Du Bois had some trouble with the truck's complicated gears and 
was oblivious to the trail of following truckers, all keeping tabs on his 
whereabouts and communicating with their CB radios, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was just trying to find the gears," said Hyer. "He was so busy trying to 
shift, he wasn't looking at anything else." 
</P>
<P>
 The truck exited on Templin Highway and proceeded west to the Old Golden State 
Highway, Moore said. Pursuing truckers spotted a California Department of 
Transportation dump truck parked nearby and radioed the California Department 
of Transportation worker to call the highway patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 Once at the intersection, Du Bois unsuccessfully tried to turn the 
tractor-trailer around. Becoming discouraged, he got out and attempted to 
disengage the trailer from the cab, Hyer said. 
</P>
<P>
 Du Bois gave up and fled the truck on foot before being apprehended by CHP 
officers. 
</P>
<P>
 Hyer said that before commandeering the truck, Du Bois slashed the tires of 
the car he drove up in and began throwing clothes from the vehicle onto the 
ground. 
</P>
<P>
 Du Bois is in custody at the Santa Clarita Valley sheriff's station. 
</P>
</TEXT>
