<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 MEN KILLED IN HEAD-ON COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men were killed on Sierra Highway shortly before rush hour when their 
vehicles collided head-on north of Mint Canyon Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Horton of Acton and Leros Hull of Valencia, both 51, died shortly after 
the 4:44 p.m. accident Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Horton's pickup truck was traveling north on Sierra Highway and pulled into 
the southbound lane, hitting Hull's car, California Highway Patrol Officer 
Wendy Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 Each vehicle was traveling 50 to 60 m.p.h. when the collision occurred. Both 
men were wearing seat belts, and the car's air bag deployed in the collision, 
Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rebecca Mercer, 26, of Lancaster was driving behind Hull and received minor 
injuries when her station wagon slid into the side of Hull's car. DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
