<P>
2 SHOT IN GANG CROSS-FIRE, POLICE SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 6-year-old girl and a 20-year-old man were shot Thursday in what police said 
was gang cross-fire in the 1900 block of West Myrtle Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Just before 6 p.m., an apparent gun battle broke out between rival gangs near 
Myrtle and Wood streets, said Sgt. Jim McDaniel of the Santa Ana gang unit. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl apparently was hit by a stray shot. Both she and the man were taken 
to a local hospital, where they were reported in fair condition Thursday night, 
police said. 
</P>
