<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. MAN'S DEATH PROBED IN L.A. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Sheriff's Department is investigating the shooting death this 
week of a Garden Grove man whose body was found west of downtown. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of Willie Williams, 25, was found about 2 a.m. Wednesday next to a 
public telephone and his car in the Windsor Hills district, said Deputy Patrick 
Hauser. 
</P>
<P>
 Hauser said two deputies spotted the body alongside the parked car in the 3900 
block of West Slauson Avenue. Williams had been shot once in the upper torso, 
Hauser said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities have no motive for the shooting, and there are no suspects. 
Williams had no criminal record, the Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
