<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEN ROB MEDICAL OFFICE, INVADE HOME OF 1 VICTIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four men armed with semiautomatic handguns and knives robbed a Westminster 
medical office Thursday, then used keys taken from one of the victims to invade 
an apartment in Huntington Beach, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbers entered the medical office in the 9000 block of Edinger Avenue 
sometime before 11 a.m., Officer Robin Kapp of the Westminster Police 
Department said. 
</P>
<P>
 Seven people inside the office were robbed of an undetermined amount of cash 
and jewelry, and tied up. Two of the assailants then took a set of keys from 
one of the victims and drove her car to her apartment in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach police said they believe the two robbers used the keys to 
enter the apartment in a large complex in the 8400 block of Edinger Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 They surprised the victim's 30-year-old husband and threatened him with a 
kitchen knife that one of them was carrying, Lt. Luis Ochoa of the Huntington 
Beach Police Department said. They put a towel over his head, tied him up, and 
ransacked the apartment of an undetermined amount of cash and jewelry, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 They then phoned the doctor's office in Westminster and informed the two other 
assailants that they were finished, Ochoa said. The men at both locations left. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim at the apartment and the victims at the doctor's office managed to 
free themselves and called police. No one was injured in either incident, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbers were described as being in their mid-20s, wearing baggy clothing 
and bandannas. Police said they were still searching for the stolen car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
